  "instructions": [
    "1. In a small saucepan, toast the Korean chili flakes over low heat for 2-3 minutes.",
    "2. In a large bowl, whisk together the toasted chili flakes, sesame oil, soy sauce, grated ginger, and rice vinegar.",
    "3. Add the namul to the bowl and toss to combine with the dressing.",
    "4. Flake the smoked mackerel into the bowl and gently fold to combine.",
    "5. Garnish with thinly sliced green onions and chopped cilantro.",
    "6. Serve immediately and enjoy!"
